Based on the Technology, Global Oxidative Stress Assay Market is divided into Enzyme-Linked Immunosorbent Assays, Chromatography, Flow Cytometry, Microscopy, and High-Content Screening. ELISA and flow cytometry, as well as some of the more recent methods, are used to detect oxidative stress in the body, as well as other vitals and composition information. In 2017, the ELISA segment dominated the global market owing to the high adoption of the assays and better specificity and sensitivity.

Based on the Diseases, Global Oxidative Stress Assays market is divided into cardiovascular diseases, cancer, neural diseases, respiratory diseases, and other diseases based on disease type. Because of the high and increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases around the world, the cardiovascular diseases segment accounted for the largest share of this market in 2020.

Based on the End-users, the healthcare industry, pharmaceutical industry, and research institutes are the primary End-Users of the Global Oxidative Stress Assay Market. The biopharmaceutical industries and biotechnology sector are the major users of oxidative assays within the pharmaceutical industry. With the growing advancements in drug discovery, the global pharmaceutical industry grew at a CAGR of 8.8% in 2020. Another area of importance for oxidative stress detection in healthcare diagnostics, which has been gaining importance over the past five years and improving its infrastructure since 2010 in most countries. The steady growth of these end-users of oxidative stress assays will drive the demand for these products and solutions during the forecast period.
